&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is for internal candidates to South Tees Trust. If you are not currently working within the trust your application will not be reviewed and automatically rejected at shortlisting stage. Please be aware of this when submitting your application.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5 Hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint a keen and enthusiastic Senior Neuroradiographer to join our friendly, specialist team. It is an excellent opportunity for a radiographer who is interested in a specialist field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to have some CT, MRI and/or Vascular experience, as they will be expected to rotate through all the modalities within the department. There is an on-call and an extended day service in place and this can be discussed further at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neuroradiology department offers a tertiary imaging service to over 1 million people. It currently provides CT, MR, Interventional Neuroradiology to the Neurosciences Directorate, in addition to numerous services to the ENT, Ophthalmology, Oral Surgery and Max Fax.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 3T MR scanner is involved in joint research with the University of Durham and the successful candidate will have the chance to be involved in this programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Richard Bore (Principal Clinical Neuroradiographer)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: richard.bore@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 854284&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
